Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_oa_library_property(25.10)                  add_oa_library_property(25.10)

Name
       add_oa_library_property  - Adds a new property to the specified OpenAc-
       cess library

Syntax
       add_oa_library_property

       [-help]

       -lib <libName>

       -name <prop_name>

        -type {boolean integer float string}

       -value <propValue>

       Adds a new property to the specified OpenAccess library.  This  command
       cannot be used to change the value of an existing property.

       Note:  You  cannot  use  the  name techLibName for the property you are
       adding because this name is used by the  OpenAccess  infrastructure  to
       store the property attached to the library.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each add_oa_library_property parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man add_oa_library_property.

       -lib <libName>
              Specifies  the name of the OpenAccess library to which the prop-
              erty has to be added.

       -name <prop_name>
              Specifies the name of the property being created.

       -type {boolean integer float string}
              Specifies the type of the property being created.

       -value <propValue>
              Specifies the value to be set for property  being  created.  The
              value  is interpreted from the input string and converted to the
              specified type.

Example
       In Innovus, the following set  of  commands  creates  a  library  named
       <myLib>,  adds  the <prop1> property to it, and saves the design before
       exiting:

       createLib myLib -attachTech adiTech

       add_oa_lib_property -lib myLib -name prop1 -type string -value value1

       saveDesign -cellview {myLib block1 layout}

       exit

       You can now add more properties to the library in  Virtuoso.  When  you
       restore  the  design in Innovus, all properties previously added to the
       library, whether in Innovus or Virtuoso, reflect correctly.

Related Information
